The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     IN THE CITY
                  
	 The Cricket Association of Bengal (CAB) has sounded out Woorkeri Raman to take over as Bengal coach, CAB joint secretary Samar Pal said on Tuesday. Pal said he had spoken to Raman during a meeting in Chennai recently. Raman has previously coached Bengal for two seasons.                
	 Mahima Dey and Pinky Agarwal reached the girls final in the Stag-WBTTA table tennis summer camp 2008. Jeet Chandra and Krishnendu Sarkar will meet in the final of the boys section while the final of the kids section will be played between Raika Saha and Sneha Mahapatra.                
	CRICKET: CAB Ambar Roy sub-junior final from 2 pm.      
	TABLE TENNIS: Stag-WBTTA summer camp 2008, finals from 4pm.                                                                                                                                                                     
